@page "/"

<PageTitle>OpenCvSharp Blazor Sample</PageTitle>

<h1>OpenCvSharp + Blazor WebAssembly</h1>

<p>
    Code samples showing <a href="https://github.com/shimat/opencvsharp" target="_blank">OpenCvSharp</a>
    running entirely in the browser via Blazor WebAssembly - no server-side processing involved.
</p>

<ul>
    <li><a href="build-info">Build Info</a> - the OpenCV build compiled into this app's WebAssembly binary</li>
    <li><a href="opencvsharp_sample">Filters</a> - load an image and run a few basic OpenCV operations (pseudo-color, threshold, edge detection) on it</li>
    <li><a href="samples/features">Keypoints &amp; Matching</a> - AKAZE keypoint detection and feature matching between two images</li>
    <li><a href="samples/detection">Live Face Detection</a> - real-time face detection against a live webcam feed</li>
    <li><a href="samples/interactive">GrabCut Segmentation</a> - drag a rectangle to extract the foreground from an image</li>
</ul>
